==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Galipot
<hw>Gal"i*pot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>galipot</ets>; cf. OF. <ets>garipot</ets> the wild pine or pitch
tree.]</ety> <def>An impure resin of turpentine, hardened on the outside
of pine trees by the spontaneous evaporation of its essential oil. When
purified, it is called <xex>yellow pitch</xex>, <xex>white pitch</xex>,
or <xex>Burgundy pitch</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gall</ent>⟦br⟧
